## Usage Patterns

### Pattern 1: Starting a New Component

```markdown
BEFORE CODING:

1. Check PRD.md:

   - Section: "Feature X: Component Name"
   - Read: User Story, Acceptance Criteria, Technical Specs
   - Note: Success Metrics

2. Check CREATIVE_DECISIONS.md:

   - Find: ADR for relevant pattern (e.g., ADR-004 Component Naming)
   - Apply: Naming conventions, file structure
   - Use: Code examples as templates

3. Implement:

   - File location: Follow ADR-004 (feature-based grouping)
   - Component name: Follow naming convention
   - Props/types: Match PRD technical specs
   - Acceptance criteria: Implement ALL items

4. Verify:
   - ✅ All acceptance criteria met
   - ✅ ADR patterns followed
   - ✅ Success metrics achievable
   - ✅ Code matches examples
```

### Pattern 2: Implementing Data Fetching

````markdown
BEFORE CODING:

1. Check PRD.md:

   - Section: "8. Data Requirements"
   - Review: Data models (TypeScript types)
   - Note: Fetch strategies

2. Check CREATIVE_DECISIONS.md:

   - ADR-002: Lazy Loading Strategy
   - ADR-005: React Query Configuration
   - Apply: Stale times, cache times, enabled flags

3. Implement:
   ```typescript
   // Follow ADR-005 pattern exactly
   const { data } = useProjectAddons(projectId, {
     enabled: isAddonsPageActive, // Lazy load (ADR-002)
     staleTime: 2 * 60 * 1000, // 2 min (ADR-005)
   })
   ```
````

4. Verify:
   - ✅ Lazy loading works (ADR-002)
   - ✅ Cache configuration correct (ADR-005)
   - ✅ Data model matches PRD types

````

### Pattern 3: Building a Page

```markdown
STEP-BY-STEP WITH PRD/ADR:

Phase 1: Read Requirements
├── PRD.md → Find "Feature X: Page Name"
│   ├── User Story: Understand user goal
│   ├── Acceptance Criteria: Checklist of features
│   ├── Technical Specs: Components, data, layout
│   └── Success Metrics: Performance targets
└── CREATIVE_DECISIONS.md → Find related ADRs
    ├── ADR-001: Sidebar pattern (if applicable)
    ├── ADR-002: Data loading strategy
    ├── ADR-004: Component naming
    └── ADR-006: Route structure

Phase 2: Plan Implementation
├── File location: Apply ADR-004 (naming conventions)
├── Route setup: Apply ADR-006 (nested routes)
├── Data fetching: Apply ADR-002, ADR-005
└── Error handling: Apply ADR-008

Phase 3: Implement
├── Create component with PRD technical specs
├── Implement ALL acceptance criteria items
├── Follow ADR code examples
└── Use PRD data models (TypeScript types)

Phase 4: Verify
├── Acceptance criteria: All checkboxes ✅
├── Success metrics: Load time, interaction speed
├── ADR compliance: Patterns followed
└── Update Memory Bank: Mark task complete
````

